        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Seeing that no one else has cared to reply yet, I suppose I'm obligated to educate you about the spiriling road of darkness that we call a necromancer life, young one.  Basically, weapons never increased damage per hit, but could increase attack speed.  Two FS daggers would give our pet an effective 40% haste, not bad eh? Combined with our nice pet buffs (augmentation of death or the lesser augment death) we could pull off 105% haste!  However, this IS VI that made the game...so they decided to nerf us, pretty much out of the blue, even after we suffered tons of other pet nerfs in the past (49 pet hit for 71 back in the day, now only 49 max I believe...pets used to have npc regen rates too!).  There was a patch a while back that made it so that no matter what weapon you give your pet, it has no effect.  Oh well, I still love playing a necro.  We're a kick ass class and can out-solo anyone else, quadding or not.  I routinely triple kite, and fear kiting no longer gives xp to our pet.  I love to pull an entire 4 camp spawn just as a druid gets ready to quad...they give me dirty looks as I snare, dot, and fear them all and my pet beats them down in seconds like a blood thirsty demon from hell =)  ah well sorry bout the ranting, I'm pissed about our nerfs but we're still great to play!</P><P> </font></td>
