        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Unless they changed this (admittedly, it's been a while since I was a baby Romancer).. the lowest level pets do accept weapons, and will (to a degree) use the damage/delay ratio. Even after the nerf of FS daggers to a min delay of .. I think it was 6? .. you could still give a pet a 2h 12damage FS sword and you would see his damage increase (using an example here, forgive me for a bad memory) from like 20 to 28 damage per swing, but it would be much slower than he normally hit. I loved doing this every chance I could find an extra 2hs in Unrest or wherever I was at the time.  You know, I'm 'pretty' sure this still works.. it's not a huge advantage or anything, but it's fun to see your pet (at level 12) hitting for more damage than normal when you give him a giant 2hander.</P><P><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i></font></td>
